<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="aurifolia">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea aurifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but leaves oblong, rather than lanceolate, narrower (&lt;7 mm wide) and much more thinly hairy, outer sepals acuminate and the inflorescence more strictly terminal.
</paragraph>
